  "texts": [
    "The terms δ1 and δ1 represent exogenous disturbance terms.",
    "λ1, λ2, λ3 and λ4 are the correlations between the indicators and latent variable.",
    "We include θ1, θ2, θ3 and θ4, which are not part of a standard measurement model, to represent the lags between the latent variable and indicators.",
    "ϵ1, ϵ2, ϵ3 and ϵ4 take their usual meaning in SEM as measurement error terms.",
    "SEM does not have a convention for representing causal relationships involving accumulations of rates of change, which has led to some confusion in trying to estimate causal effects that affect state variables as direct effects other than a rate of change."
